  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-04 drift)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Validation results were generated under ModelConfiguration ansys-cfx-2026-q1-build-7-rc2, which the assessment team characterised as effectively identical to the released build ansys-cfx-2026-q1-build-7. No re-run was performed under the released version; the drift is a single patch-level revision that introduces minor turbulence-model coefficient updates.",
