      "name": "Absolute hemolysis index validation against FDA pump benchtop data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalised index of haemolysis (NIH) values compared against benchtop measurements across 5 flow-speed operating points. Mean absolute error 0.0041 g/100 L, within the 0.005 g/100 L acceptance band. Monte Carlo UQ (n=2000) confirms 95th-percentile NIH remains below clinical threshold. Validation was executed under ModelConfiguration ansys-cfx-2026-q1-build-7-rc2, one patch revision prior to the released solver build. The assessment team noted that the only change between rc2 and the released build was a correction to the SST turbulence-model free-stream omega limiter; internal benchmarking showed less than 0.3% difference in bulk velocity fields on a canonical pipe case and the team concluded re-running was unnecessary.",
